block.more_orn_plants.green_calyx_mei_wa: Green Calyx Mei Wall Hanging Sign
block.more_orn_plants.double_pink_mei_wa: Double Pink Mei Wall Hanging Sign
advancement.moreornplants.root.title: The Florilegium
advancement.moreornplants.root.descripti: Each bloom in its season, a perfect sight; Wrought by the hand of heaven and earth.
advancement.moreornplants.the_leader_amo: She heralds spring, not rivals it; Smiles midst blooms when mountains are lit.
advancement.moreornplants.the_winter_gue: Golden buds in spring‘s chill confined, A fragrance vexing, yet to unwind.
advancement.moreornplants.flower_king.de: When the Peony sways, The capital's ablaze.
advancement.moreornplants.flower_chancel: A grace to behold, Seeing spring to its fold.
advancement.moreornplants.flower_queen.d: No day without a breeze, No day this flower doesn't please.
advancement.moreornplants.regal_fragranc: The orchid, unseen, on the mountain high, Is painted by lovers 'neath windows' eye.
When all other blooms are past and gone, In this flower, autumn's reign lingers on.
advancement.moreornplants.celestial_cons: Lest midnight steal the blooms' delight; I burn a candle to prolong the night.
advancement.moreornplants.fragrance_afar: Soft in tint, demure in hue, A fragrance sweet, the whole way through.
advancement.moreornplants.flower_scholar: Peach and plum, fair and bright; Can't match my branch, in spring's delight!
advancement.moreornplants.wuling_vista.d: Graceful the peach tree; Dazzling its flowers.
advancement.moreornplants.pear_in_rain.d: A jade-like face, with lonely tears bespread, A pear blossom weeping in the spring rain.
advancement.moreornplants.aura_from_east: You throw a peach to me; I give a plum in glee.
The phoenix sings, on peak so high, The tree bathes in morning's dye.
advancement.moreornplants.lotus_sage.des: Leaves merge with skies in endless jade expanse; Blooms bathed in sun gain a transcendent glance.
advancement.moreornplants.hundred_day_re: Who sits with me at dusk? Alone, With my tree, until the day is done.
advancement.moreornplants.lasting_beauty: While others fade, it stands the test, And blooms anew, while having rest.
The cuckoo's cry, the blooms so bright, In distant lands, a shared delight.
advancement.moreornplants.the_frost_defi: By countless waters, Cotton Roses grace, Their rouge, by dawn’s light dew, still pale of face.
advancement.moreornplants.flower_gallant: Its splendor puts all art to shame, Who gave the name 'Rose' to this flame?
Grasses recall the hero's tale, Of the song that on the river did fail.
advancement.moreornplants.flower_melanch: No word from far-off clouded land, The lilac knots in rain, unplanned.
advancement.moreornplants.flower_loyalis: As nature's law, it cannot be undone, This flower turns to face the rising sun.
As tribute to the throne, its precious fruit was borne.
Deep in the wild, it slowly grows, its worth the world foreknows.
advancement.moreornplants.riverside_beac: Under the setting moon, the crows cry in the frosty sky, by maples and the fisher's fire, in sorrow I lie.
advancement.moreornplants.chinaberry_win:
I blamed the south wind for blowing purple snow,
Unaware ’twas Chinaberry blooms in flight, by the eaves’ side.
advancement.moreornplants.hero_of_desert:
A thousand years standing alive,
a thousand years standing dead,
a thousand years enduring fallen.
advancement.moreornplants.grasses.title: Lush and Gone, Year by Year
advancement.moreornplants.grasses.descri: No wildfire can burn it all away, it returns with the breeze of spring day.
advancement.moreornplants.four_gentlemen: Unite the four: Mei, Cymbidium, Bamboo, and Chrysanthemum.
advancement.moreornplants.offer_chrysant:
Its fragrance drifts, with dew from paths imbued;
The reader pauses, in autumn's quiet mood.
advancement.moreornplants.tread_snow_see:
Outshone in white by snowdrifts pure and deep,
The Mei outdoes them all with fragrance sweet to keep.
advancement.moreornplants.white_snow_red: A Crystal World of Snow and Blossoms
advancement.moreornplants.fragrant_snow_:
Afar, I see a gleam of snow? Nay, not quite,
For a hidden fragrance steals upon the night.
advancement.moreornplants.peach_blossom_:
Through the grove, a sudden sight,
Peach blossoms adrift, pure and bright.
advancement.moreornplants.flowers_as_mat:
The garden stirs with spring's delight,
All blossoms pale when you're in view.
advancement.moreornplants.crimson_highla:
O, Azaleas！Blaze ever bright!
A revolutionary flame, forever in bloom.
advancement.moreornplants.cottonrose_rea:
Autumn winds o'er the Cottonrose Realm vast and wide;
Evening rain cloaks a village where climbing figs bide.
advancement.moreornplants.little_iron_th:
To bear the world’s chill, red snow I take my leave;
To leave the dust, fragrant purple clouds I cleave and receive.
advancement.moreornplants.peach_blossom_: Peach Blossoms of the Secluded Temple

In the Cove of Peach Blooms stands the Hermitage fair;
In the Hermitage dwells an immortal, free from care.
advancement.moreornplants.apricot_villag:
“Where might an inn be?” A question thrown. 
A cowherd points afar where apricots have grown.
tooltip.more_orn_plants.mod_bamboo.toolt:
§7Ornamental varieties,
non-building material,
pandas don't like to eat
